THIRD-PARTY DATA NOTICE

This MIT license covers the original simulation source code in this repository.
It does NOT purport to license the third-party scientific data embedded or
referenced by the code, which carries its own terms:

  * Lunar gravity field (lunar_gravity_coeffs.py): spherical-harmonic
    coefficients derived from the GRAIL GRGM1200A model produced by NASA's
    Gravity Recovery and Interior Laboratory mission. NASA data products are
    generally free of copyright and in the public domain in the United States;
    they are reproduced here for scientific reproducibility. See the NASA
    Planetary Data System (PDS) Geosciences Node for the authoritative model.

  * Lunar/solar ephemeris: computed from the Meeus analytic series; planetary
    constants and the November-2022 Artemis I flight-reference values are drawn
    from public NASA mission documentation.

  * As-flown trajectory (data/artemis1_ephemeris/): the Orion Orbit Ephemeris
    Message (OEM) for Artemis I, a public NASA data product, used solely as the
    ground-truth gauge for the trajectory-fidelity comparison.

No claim of ownership is made over any NASA-origin data. Users redistributing
this repository should preserve this notice.
